      "title": "Nonlinear nature of gravitation and gravitational-wave experiments",
      "abstract": "It is shown that gravitational waves from astronomical sources have a nonlinear erect on laser interferometer detectors on Earth, an erect which has hitherto been neglected, but which is of the same order of magnitude as the linear erects. The signature of the nonlinear erect is a permanent displacement of test masses after the passage of a wave train"
